                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d698">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2451: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-09T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 9, 1922—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 10—9:12 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>To Stevens. My January 10, 6 p.m.<note n="64" xml:id="d698fn64">Not
                        printed.</note> Wang Nai-pin has refused to take office as president [<hi
                        rend="italic">director general</hi>] of the Chinese Eastern <pb facs="1009"
                        n="889" xml:id="pg_889"/> Railway. Because of fear that the power of the
                    Technical Board will be broadened no other Chinese of the old school is willing
                    to accept the position, so Dr. C. C. Wang has been appointed as acting head of
                    the railway.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
